Changes from 1.3.1 to 1.4 - released 2012/3/25

- Upgrade to geshi 18.1.0, with many new languages
- New: take over links to "view template" in debug output, via jQuery. Applies to css, js and php files aw well
- Fix line end characters in all php files part of the extension. Was causing errors on some linux platforms
- New: add a list of blacklisted files/dirs for file highligting via module/view
- Added a workaround for ini file highlighting problems when the 1st line is not a php opening tag
- Fix: allow usage of absolute paths on windows for the highlighting view

- Incompatible change: usage of absolute paths for the highlighting is disallowed
  by default and has to be enabled via a configuration parameter in ezsh.ini
